<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>There are lots of solutions, Q is what will Verant do for us?</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?TheBlack[BCK]">TheBlack[BCK]</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 4:51 p.m. 11/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> There are lots of solutions, Q is what will Verant do for us?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=700" TARGET=_self>Then please read on....</A> (Min)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>I think you should approach Verant and ask them what the are and are not willing to do to support the PvP community. There are a lot ofchanges and improvements that can be added to make PvP a workable system in Everquest, the real question is what can Brad and the dev team do for us in the near future? I understand they are very busy with bug fixes and getting the game out the door. Be that as it may, will the PvP community have a chance? Will Verant help us by changing some of the algorithms for PVP specific combat?
<P>Once we know what limitations we are working under we can better address possible solutions. If the worse case scenario is true, and no additional changes or support are intended for PvP in everquest, then by all means let us know now so we can go to the -PvP servers and try to enjoy that aspect of the game, rather than waste further time and effort on these discussions.
<P>&gt; I think a lot of people have expressed the sentiment about
<BR>&gt; levels being too much a factor in PvP, I tend to agree with
<BR>&gt; them. The fun about PvP is that anything goes, you don't have be
<BR>&gt; a LV40+ in order to be able to kill, right now as people have
<BR>&gt; tested, when you are just a couple levels below someone your
<BR>&gt; spells will fail on them about like 80%, this level-dependancy
<BR>&gt; is too harsh in my opinion and would result in a high level
<BR>&gt; group being nearly invincible. Some people have suggested the
<BR>&gt; idea that magic resistance be a fixed value without regard to
<BR>&gt; levels, some believe that a more skill-oriented system is better
<BR>&gt; than a level-oriented system(I tend to agree with this one),
<BR>&gt; some suggest removing the bonus from levels altogether.
<P>&gt; My suggestion for magic resistance would be it should be a
<BR>&gt; number calculated from your race+class+int/wis(I know it sounds
<BR>&gt; like D&D heheheh), remove resistance bonus from Levels, and add
<BR>&gt; a magic resistance skill which you can train that would be a
<BR>&gt; nice little bonus rather than a drastic bonus. Any comments
<BR>&gt; welcomed.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
